  <p>The place was narrow and had black matte-finished walls.The next step they took, a sword came flying. Crater asked, â€œShould we really go this way? Isnâ€™t there any other way to go?â€ in a horrified way. Carter replied, â€œIf it was easy, It wouldnâ€™t be a treasure-hunt or I wouldnâ€™t have comeâ€. Crater yelled at him in Gibberish. Crater told Carter to open Chapter 22 - page 85 - The struggle to the treasure in the book. Carter opened the page and said, â€œWow! Someone has an interest in this but you shouldâ€™ve told this before because it has info about the flying swordâ€. Crater said, â€œItâ€™s a Do or Die situation, so I had to remember itâ€. Carter said, â€œThe next obstacle is an arrow walk Luckily we have how-to-reach-the-end-aliveâ€. They followed the rules as it is in the book. The next obstacle was slicing blades and they were told to stand in between the lines in which the sharp blades will come. The next one was swallowing sand and it said to walk on the edges of the floor where the sand was absent. And Thatâ€™s it they have reached the end of the book and the treasure cave. Crater asked, â€œWhere is the treasure?â€. Carter replied, â€œI-I-I am not sure. Like the book has ended as well as the wayâ€.</p>
  <p>They waited there for a few minutes and Crater went and lit a flame-torch. He found something different in the wall when the light touched the wall. He asked, â€œCarter, You still have the UV torch, right? Can you pass it?â€. Carter then passed the UV torch to him. Crater hit the UV light in the wall and called Carter to see this amazing thing. They saw an arrow which pointed to a human-sized box. There was a dot to the east side of the box and above it was written â€˜PRESS HEREâ€™. Carter pressed in the dot. The wall along the line of the box went in and some air went in due to air pressure which blew the fire in the flame-torch. Now also the room was empty. Crater said, â€œWhat? It-Itâ€™s Empty, but why?â€. Carter said, â€œNo, look thereâ€, He pointed at a place using the UV light. There was a rectangular box. Carter said, â€œGive me the bookâ€. Crater replied, â€œWhat book? Oh that one, One secondâ€. Carter kept the book in the hole and pushed it in. The door through which they came in, closed and a new door in front of them opened and again due to air pressure, a force pulled them inside and closed the door. They woke up and guess what? Yes, They finally found the treasure. The treasure room was as big as half of a football stadium. The driver congratulated both of them for finding the treasure. Carter couldnâ€™t be in a place because of his happiness but Carter put one rule, â€˜No one touches any of the treasuresâ€™. Crater took a beautiful dagger that was clean and sharp which made him disobey the one and only rule of Carter. They found a ladder going up in the end of the treasure room. They went up in it and it led to the top of the banyan tree near which they landed their helicopter. Carter said, â€œI didnâ€™t expect thisâ€. It was night so they slept in the helicopter.</p>
